20/06/2004
BUCHAREST, Romania -- An EBRD delegation in Bucharest said Friday (18 June) that Romania has registered strong economic progress, but added that the transition process has not ended.
The delegation met with President Ion Iliescu, Public Finance Minister Mihai Tanasescu and Economy Minister Dan Ioan Popescu.
The EBRD is calling for additional reforms in the banking system and energy sector.
(Mediafax - 18/06/04)
